---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../config';

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is Allowed to Keep Terms (ATKT)?",
    answer: "Allowed to Keep Terms (ATKT) is an academic progression system in Indian universities, including Mumbai University. It allows students who have failed in a limited number of subjects (or heads of passing) to proceed to the next semester or academic year, on the condition that they clear those backlog exams in subsequent semesters."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the Year Drop (academic detention) rule at Mumbai University?",
    answer: "A Year Drop (or Year Down) is a forced academic detention where a student is not allowed to register for the next academic year. Under MU regulations, this happens if a student fails to clear all backlog subjects from the previous-to-previous academic year (e.g., you cannot enter the 3rd Year if you still have even 1 backlog left from the 1st Year) or if they exceed the maximum allowed current-year backlogs (e.g., more than 8 heads of passing in MU Engineering)."
  },
  {
    question: "How do credit requirements work under the NEP 2020 rules for Mumbai University?",
    answer: "Under the National Education Policy (NEP 2020) rules introduced for Mumbai University, promotion is credit-based. Instead of counting failed heads of passing, students must earn a minimum cumulative credit threshold. For example, to progress from First Year to Second Year, a student must secure at least 32 cumulative credits out of 40 or 44 total year credits."
  },
  {
    question: "Do internal assessments and theory papers count as separate ATKT backlogs?",
    answer: "Yes. In professional courses like Mumbai University Engineering (C-Scheme / R-2019), internal assessments (IA/unit tests, practicals, oral/viva, and term work) and end-semester theory examinations (ESE) are treated as separate 'heads of passing'. Failing in either component counts as one failed head, even if they belong to the same subject."
  },
  {
    question: "What are Ordinances 5042 and 5045 for grace marks?",
    answer: "Ordinance 5042 provides grace marks for passing a head of passing (up to 1% of total aggregate marks, or a maximum of 5–10 marks depending on the syllabus). Ordinance 5045 is for condonation of deficiencies, allowing up to 10 marks to be distributed across a maximum of two passing heads if a student is failing in those subjects."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I enter the final year if I have a second-year backlog?",
    answer: "No. Under the year-clearance ordinance, you must completely pass all subjects from both the First Year (Sem 1 & 2) and Second Year (Sem 3 & 4) before you are allowed to enter the Fourth Year (Sem 7). A single outstanding backlog from these years will result in a Year Drop, even if your Third-Year marks are clear."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I take admission to next year with KT?",
    answer: "Yes. Under ATKT (Allowed to Keep Terms) rules, you can secure provisional admission to the next academic year even if you have active backlogs (KTs), provided the total number of KTs is within the permitted limits (e.g., ≤ 8 failed heads for Mumbai University Engineering, or ≤ 2 failed subjects per semester for B.Sc/B.Com/B.A)."
  },
  {
    question: "How many KTs are allowed in Mumbai University?",
    answer: "In MU Engineering (C-Scheme), you are allowed up to 8 failed heads of passing per academic year, with a maximum of 5 being end-semester theory papers (ESE). In MU General Degree courses (B.Sc/B.Com/B.A), you are allowed a maximum of 2 failed subjects per semester. In NEP 2020 programs, ATKT is credit-based: you must secure at least 32/44 credits in Year 1 to enter Year 2, and 76/88 credits overall to enter Year 3."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the difference between ATKT and Year Down?",
    answer: "ATKT is a provisional promotion that lets you attend classes in the next year while carrying backlog subjects. A Year Down (academic detention) means you have exceeded the allowable backlogs or have failed to clear prior year backlogs. During a Year Down, you cannot take admission to the next year and must sit out to clear your pending papers."
  },
  {
    question: "What exactly is a Head of Passing?",
    answer: "A head of passing is any academic evaluation unit that requires a separate minimum score to pass. For example, in a single subject, the end-semester theory exam (ESE), internal assessment (IA/term work), oral exam/viva, and practical exam are all separate heads of passing. Failing in any one of these means you have a KT in that specific head."
  },
  {
    question: "Can a practical KT cause a Year Down?",
    answer: "Yes. Because practicals and term work (TW) are separate heads of passing, failing them counts as a backlog/KT. If your cumulative failed heads (theory + practicals + internals) exceed 8, or if you fail to clear a prior-year practical head before entering the 3rd or 4th year, it will trigger a Year Down."
  },
  {
    question: "Can grace marks save me from a Year Down?",
    answer: "Yes, Mumbai University has specific ordinances (O.5042 and O.5045) that allow examiners to award grace marks (usually up to 1% of total year marks or 10 marks distributed across subjects) if they enable you to pass a subject and avoid academic detention (Year Down)."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I sit for placements with an active KT?",
    answer: "Most top-tier companies visiting campuses for placements require students to have 'Zero Active Backlogs' (0 active KTs) at the time of recruitment. Some companies may also enforce a 'No History of Backlogs' policy. It is highly recommended to clear all ATKTs in the regular and supplementary exam cycles before your final year placement season begins."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="ATKT & Backlog Eligibility Helper"
  description="Check your ATKT status and backlog promotion eligibility. Calculate whether you face a Year Drop under Mumbai University Engineering, B.Sc, B.Com, and NEP 2020 rules."
  {faq}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <nav class="flex mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] text-mute">
        <li>
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-ink transition-colors">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-1.5 select-none">
          <span>/</span>
          <span class="text-body font-semibold">ATKT Eligibility Helper</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
        <span class="rounded-full border border-hairline bg-canvas px-3 py-1 font-mono text-[11px] font-semibold text-mute">
          Tool 05
        </span>
        <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">
          Academic Standings Planner
        </span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-sans text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] text-ink sm:text-4xl">
        ATKT & Backlog Eligibility Helper
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        Check your academic progression standing in seconds. Analyze whether you are eligible to keep terms (ATKT) or face a Year Drop under Mumbai University C-Scheme, General Degree CBCS, and NEP 2020 credit regulations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Tool Workspace -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12">
      <!-- Calculator Inputs -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 lg:col-span-7">
        
        <!-- Setup Card -->
        <div class="rounded-md border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4 sm:p-6 shadow-level-2 transition-colors duration-200">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-6">
            Academic Standings Setup
          </h2>

          <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
            <!-- Program / University Preset Selector -->
            <div>
              <label for="scheme-selector" class="block text-sm font-medium text-ink mb-2">
                University Regulations / Scheme
              </label>
              <select
                id="scheme-selector"
                class="w-full h-10 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-3 text-sm text-ink focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-primary appearance-none cursor-pointer"
              >
                <option value="mu-engg">Mumbai University Engineering (C-Scheme / Heads of Passing)</option>
                <option value="mu-degree">Mumbai University B.Sc / B.Com / B.A (CBCS - 2 per Sem Limit)</option>
                <option value="mu-nep">Mumbai University NEP-2020 (Credit-Based Progression)</option>
                <option value="autonomous">Autonomous College (Carry-over & Golden KT Tracker)</option>
                <option value="custom">Custom Rules (Configure custom limits...)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Target Year Selector -->
            <div>
              <label for="target-selector" class="block text-sm font-medium text-ink mb-2">
                Promotion Check
              </label>
              <select
                id="target-selector"
                class="w-full h-10 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-3 text-sm text-ink focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-primary appearance-none cursor-pointer"
              >
                <option value="y1-y2">Sem 2 ➔ Sem 3 (Admission to Second Year)</option>
                <option value="y2-y3">Sem 4 ➔ Sem 5 (Admission to Third Year)</option>
                <option value="y3-y4">Sem 6 ➔ Sem 7 (Admission to Fourth Year)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Dynamic Input Panels based on scheme -->
            
            <!-- 1. Prior Year Clearance (Shown for Y2-Y3 and Y3-Y4 targets) -->
            <div id="prior-clearance-panel" class="hidden border-t border-hairline pt-4">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-2">
                Prior Academic History
              </label>
              <div class="rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <span class="block text-sm font-medium text-ink mb-2" id="prior-clearance-label">
                  Have you completely cleared all subjects from previous years?
                </span>
                <div class="flex gap-4">
                  <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-body cursor-pointer">
                    <input type="radio" name="prior-clear" id="prior-clear-yes" value="yes" checked class="accent-primary h-4 w-4" />
                    <span>Yes, 100% Cleared (0 outstanding KTs)</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-body cursor-pointer">
                    <input type="radio" name="prior-clear" id="prior-clear-no" value="no" class="accent-primary h-4 w-4" />
                    <span>No, I have active KTs</span>
                  </label>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 2. MU Engineering Heads of Passing Counters -->
            <div id="mu-engg-panel" class="flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
                <span>Current Year Outstanding Failed Heads</span>
                <span id="engg-sync-note" class="hidden text-[10px] text-link font-sans font-normal normal-case animate-fade-in">(synced from logger)</span>
              </label>
              <p class="text-xs text-mute leading-normal mb-2">
                Select the number of failed components/heads of passing in the current year. (Theory papers and internals count separately).
              </p>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div>
                  <label for="failed-ese" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed End-Sem Theory (ESE) Exams</label>
                  <input type="number" id="failed-ese" value="0" min="0" max="20" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="failed-internal" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed Internals / Practicals / TW / Viva</label>
                  <input type="number" id="failed-internal" value="0" min="0" max="25" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 3. MU General Degree Subject Counters -->
            <div id="mu-degree-panel" class="hidden flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
                <span>Current Year Failed Subjects</span>
                <span id="degree-sync-note" class="hidden text-[10px] text-link font-sans font-normal normal-case animate-fade-in">(synced from logger)</span>
              </label>
              <p class="text-xs text-mute leading-normal mb-2">
                Enter the number of failed subjects in each semester of the current year (limit is 2 subjects per semester).
              </p>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div>
                  <label for="failed-odd-sem" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium" id="label-odd-sem">Failed Subjects in Odd Sem</label>
                  <input type="number" id="failed-odd-sem" value="0" min="0" max="10" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="failed-even-sem" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium" id="label-even-sem">Failed Subjects in Even Sem</label>
                  <input type="number" id="failed-even-sem" value="0" min="0" max="10" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 4. MU NEP 2020 Credit Progression -->
            <div id="mu-nep-panel" class="hidden flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-1">
                NEP Credit Progression
              </label>
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-ink" id="credits-label">Cumulative Earned Credits</span>
                <span id="credits-required-badge" class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold text-success bg-success/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Requires Min 32/44</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <input
                  type="range"
                  id="credits-range"
                  min="0"
                  max="44"
                  value="32"
                  step="1"
                  class="h-1.5 flex-1 cursor-pointer appearance-none rounded-full bg-canvas-soft-2 accent-primary"
                  aria-label="Earned credits slider"
                />
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="credits-num"
                  value="32"
                  min="0"
                  max="44"
                  class="h-8 w-14 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas text-center text-xs font-semibold text-ink focus:outline-none"
                />
                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-mute font-semibold" id="credits-max-val">/ 44</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 5. Custom Rules Setup -->
            <div id="custom-panel" class="hidden flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-2 flex items-center justify-between">
                <span>Configure Custom ATKT Rules</span>
                <span id="custom-sync-note" class="hidden text-[10px] text-link font-sans font-normal normal-case animate-fade-in">(synced from logger)</span>
              </label>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-body cursor-pointer">
                  <input type="checkbox" id="custom-req-prior" checked class="accent-primary h-4 w-4" />
                  <span>Require Prior Years Clear?</span>
                </label>
                <div>
                  <label for="custom-max-heads" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Max Failed Heads Allowed</label>
                  <input type="number" id="custom-max-heads" value="8" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="custom-max-ese" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Max Failed ESE (Theory) Allowed</label>
                  <input type="number" id="custom-max-ese" value="5" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="custom-min-credits" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Min Credits Required (0 to ignore)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="custom-min-credits" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Custom Inputs -->
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-2">
                <div>
                  <label for="custom-input-heads" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed Heads (Current Year)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="custom-input-heads" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="custom-input-ese" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed ESE (Current Year)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="custom-input-ese" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div class="sm:col-span-2">
                  <label for="custom-input-credits" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Earned Credits / Total Credits</label>
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <input type="number" id="custom-input-credits" value="0" min="0" class="w-20 h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                    <span class="text-xs text-mute">out of</span>
                    <input type="number" id="custom-input-total-credits" value="0" min="0" class="w-20 h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                  </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 6. Autonomous College Rules Setup -->
            <div id="autonomous-panel" class="hidden flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline pt-4 animate-fade-in">
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-2 flex items-center justify-between">
                <span>Configure Autonomous College Rules</span>
                <span id="autonomous-sync-note" class="hidden text-[10px] text-link font-sans font-normal normal-case animate-fade-in">(synced from logger)</span>
              </label>

              <!-- Policy note -->
              <div class="rounded-sm border border-warning/30 bg-warning-soft/10 px-3 py-2 text-[11px] text-warning-deep leading-relaxed">
                <strong>Autonomous colleges vary widely.</strong> Configure the rules that match your college's specific ordinance — do not rely on defaults. Some colleges allow unlimited Golden KTs; some block Sem 7 entry if any Sem 3/4 KT is pending.
              </div>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-body cursor-pointer sm:col-span-2">
                  <input type="checkbox" id="autonomous-req-prior" class="accent-primary h-4 w-4" />
                  <span>Enforce Year-Clearance? <span class="text-mute">(Unchecked = Golden KTs from earlier years are allowed)</span></span>
                </label>
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-max-heads" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Max Failed Heads Allowed (current year, 0 = unlimited)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-max-heads" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-max-ese" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Max Failed ESE (Theory) Allowed (0 = unlimited)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-max-ese" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-max-golden" class="block text-[10px] text-ink mb-1 font-medium">Max Golden KTs Allowed (prior years, 0 = unlimited)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-max-golden" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-8 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2 text-xs focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Manual Backlog Inputs for Autonomous Scheme -->
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-2">
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-input-heads" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed Heads (Current Year only)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-input-heads" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-input-ese" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Failed ESE Theory (Current Year)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-input-ese" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label for="autonomous-input-golden" class="block text-xs text-ink mb-1.5 font-medium">Active Golden KTs (from prior years)</label>
                  <input type="number" id="autonomous-input-golden" value="0" min="0" class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none" />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Current Semester Status Card -->
        <div id="sem-status-card" class="rounded-md border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4 sm:p-6 shadow-level-2 transition-colors duration-200">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute font-mono mb-1">
            Current Semester Status
          </h2>
          <p class="text-xs text-mute mb-5 leading-normal">
            Quick check for <strong>this semester only</strong> — can you sit for exams, and are you at risk of detention? For year-promotion eligibility, use the <strong>Academic Standings Setup</strong> tool above.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <!-- Semester Selector -->
            <div>
              <label for="current-sem" class="block text-xs font-medium text-ink mb-1.5">
                Which semester are you currently in?
              </label>
              <select
                id="current-sem"
                class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-3 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-primary appearance-none cursor-pointer"
              >
                <option value="1">Semester 1 (First Year — Odd)</option>
                <option value="2">Semester 2 (First Year — Even)</option>
                <option value="3">Semester 3 (Second Year — Odd)</option>
                <option value="4">Semester 4 (Second Year — Even)</option>
                <option value="5" selected>Semester 5 (Third Year — Odd)</option>
                <option value="6">Semester 6 (Third Year — Even)</option>
                <option value="7">Semester 7 (Final Year — Odd)</option>
                <option value="8">Semester 8 (Final Year — Even)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Failed Counts this semester -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <label for="sem-failed-ese" class="block text-xs font-medium text-ink mb-1.5">
                  Failed Theory (ESE) this sem
                </label>
                <input
                  type="number" id="sem-failed-ese" value="0" min="0" max="10"
                  class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none"
                />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="sem-failed-internal" class="block text-xs font-medium text-ink mb-1.5">
                  Failed Internals / Practicals
                </label>
                <input
                  type="number" id="sem-failed-internal" value="0" min="0" max="15"
                  class="w-full h-9 rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas px-2.5 text-xs text-ink focus:outline-none"
                />
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Result Chips -->
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mt-1">
              <!-- Can Appear -->
              <div class="rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2 p-3 flex flex-col gap-1">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Can appear for Sem</span>
                <span id="sem-appear-val" class="text-base font-bold text-success">YES</span>
                <span id="sem-appear-note" class="text-[10px] text-mute leading-tight">Exams happen regardless of backlogs</span>
              </div>
              <!-- Can Get Promoted -->
              <div class="rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2 p-3 flex flex-col gap-1">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Year Promotion</span>
                <span id="sem-promote-val" class="text-base font-bold text-success">ON TRACK</span>
                <span id="sem-promote-note" class="text-[10px] text-mute leading-tight">No year drop risk right now</span>
              </div>
              <!-- Risk Level -->
              <div class="rounded-sm border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2 p-3 flex flex-col gap-1">
                <span class="text-[10px] font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Risk Level</span>
                <span id="sem-risk-val" class="text-base font-bold text-success">LOW</span>
